Case Study: Advantages of Using AI in Government and Public Sector
Artificial Intelligence (AI) has become a transformative force across industries, and its impact on
government and public sector services is increasingly significant. Governments worldwide are
adopting AI technologies to improve efficiency, reduce costs, enhance decision-making, and
deliver better services to citizens (OECD, 2021). From predictive analytics in public health to
automated fraud detection in financial systems, AI enables governments to respond more
effectively to complex challenges.
The public sector often manages large volumes of data and must make timely decisions under
resource constraints. AI provides powerful tools to analyze data, automate repetitive processes,
and generate actionable insights (World Economic Forum, 2022). As a result, AI has the potential
to improve transparency, accountability, and service delivery.
Some of the problems or need addressed is fraud in government programs. This is a major issue
that results in billions of dollars in losses annually. Public assistance programs, tax systems, and
unemployment benefits are particularly vulnerable to fraudulent claims and identity theft.
Traditional fraud detection methods rely on manual audits and rule-based systems, which are
often inefficient and unable to detect complex fraud patterns (U.S. GAO, 2021).
