4. Improved Efficiency- Automation allows faster processing of claims and reduces workload for
employees (OECD, 2021).
5. Enhanced Public Trust- Reducing fraud increases confidence in public programs and
institutions.
Challenges and Limitations
1. Data Privacy Concerns- AI systems require access to sensitive personal data, raising concerns
about privacy and compliance (U.S. GAO, 2021).
2. Bias and Fairness- AI models may produce biased outcomes if trained on biased data (OECD,
2021).
3. Implementation Complexity- Developing AI systems requires technical expertise and
significant investment (McKinsey & Company, 2020).
4. False Positives- Incorrectly flagging legitimate claims can negatively affect citizens.
5. Data Quality Issues- Poor-quality data can lead to inaccurate predictions.
