AI offers significant advantages for government and public sector services, including improved
efficiency, cost savings, and enhanced decision-making. The case study of fraud detection
demonstrates how AI can effectively address complex challenges while delivering measurable
benefits.
However, successful implementation requires careful attention to ethical concerns, data privacy,
and system design. The proposed AI-powered citizen assistant highlights how governments can
leverage AI to improve accessibility and service delivery.
As AI continues to evolve, it will play an increasingly important role in shaping modern
governance. Understanding both its capabilities and limitations is essential for developing
effective and responsible AI systems.
